  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0d9c\u0dad \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A pension for expatriate workers",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Labor and Foreign Employment Minister Manusha Nanayakkara said that a special pension will be introduced for expatriate workers.",
        "The minister also mentioned that the pension system will be introduced in the next few weeks.",
        "The preparation of a pension scheme for expatriate workers has been discussed for many years, and the minister said that he had instructed the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau to take necessary steps to implement the pension scheme immediately with the support of the Sri Lanka Social Security Board. He also said that he will be introduced.",
        "The Minister also mentioned that the workers who are registered with the Foreign Employment Bureau and leave for foreign jobs will have the opportunity to claim this pension.",
        "The minister said that expatriate workers will be given the opportunity to pay premiums in foreign currencies and if any worker dies while paying the money, the Foreign Employment Bureau will pay the premiums and pay the benefits to the legal owners.",
        "Expatriate workers have the opportunity to get a pension ranging from Rs 20,000 to Rs 1,00,000."
      ],
